'''Pedro Atala''' is a Honduran business owner of Camosa which is the [[Deere & Company|John Deere]] distributor in [[Honduras]]. He is also president of [[Club Deportivo Motagua|CD Motagua]]<ref>[http://www.latribuna.hn/web2.0/?p=96827 Motagua pagará hoy la deuda de Mendoza] at La Tribuna {{es icon}}</ref> along with his cousin Javier Atala. His father is Pedro Atala Simón which is an emblem in Motagua. Pedro Atala Simon was the president of the national soccer team, and the national team made his first classification to the World Cup in Spain 1982.

