{{Orphan|date=February 2015}}

'''Stephan Crétier''' (born 8 August 1963) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] businessman and [[entrepreneur]]. He is the founding [[president]] and [[chief executive officer]] of GardaWorld, one of the largest privately held [[security]] provider in the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=GardaWorld - About Us|url=http://www.gardaglobal.com/en/about-us/}}</ref>

Crétier founded GardaWorld in 1995 with an investment of $25,000, which he raised by placing a [[second mortgage]] on his home.<ref>{{cite web|title=In conversation: Stephan Crétier of Garda On becoming the Wal-mart of security, and what exactly Garda is doing in the middle east|url=http://www.macleans.ca/general/on-becoming-the-wal-mart-of-security-and-what-exactly-garda-is-doing-in-the-middle-east/|accessdate=2015-02-02}}</ref> The company now generates over $3 billion in annual [[revenue]]s<ref>{{cite web|title=GardaWorld - Fast Facts|url=http://www.gardaglobal.com/en/about-us/garda-fast-facts/}}</ref> and is one of the largest [[employer]]s in the security industry, with 65,000 [[employee]]s worldwide. Over the past 20 years, Crétier has pushed the expansion of his company<ref>{{cite web|title=Overview: Sights for sore eyes The PROFIT 100 is a very tough club to join. It’s not enough to have posted a hot year or two, because the ranking of Canada’s Fastest-Growing Companies is based ...|url=http://www.profitguide.com/manage-grow/success-stories/overview-sights-for-sore-eyes-29412}}</ref> into the security and cash services sectors, having grown the company through strategic [[takeover|acquisitions]] across [[Canada]] and into the [[United States]], [[Europe]], [[Latin America]], the [[Middle East]], [[Asia]], and [[North Africa]].

Recognized as Young Entrepreneur of the Year in 1998,<ref>{{cite web|title=Stephan Cretier Chairman/President/CEO, Garda World Security Corp|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profiles/people/4184571-stephan-cretier}}</ref> Growth Leader by Profit 100 magazine for 11 consecutive years,<ref>{{cite web|title=Canada’s fastest-growing companies The Canadian economy seems to be mired in a prolonged period of subpar growth. Hardly a fertile climate, you’d think, for building growth stars. Try telling that to the PROFIT|url=http://www.profitguide.com/opportunity/canadas-fastest-growing-companies-3-30175}}</ref> and Great Entrepreneur of the Year in 2006,<ref>{{cite web|title=Company Overview of Garda World Security Corp.|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=2688779&privcapId=2673708}}</ref> Crétier was named one of Canada's Entrepreneurs of the Decade by Profit Magazine in 2009<ref>{{cite web|title=Canada’s Entrepreneurs of the Decade|url=http://www.profitguide.com/manage-grow/success-stories/canadas-entrepreneurs-of-the-decade-29660}}</ref> and recipient of the [[Queen Elizabeth II]] Diamond Jubilee Medal in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=GardaWorld - Our History|url=http://www.gardaglobal.com/en/about-us/our-history/}}</ref> He took the company private<ref>{{cite web|title=Garda World Security founder leads company buyout|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/globe-investor/garda-world-security-founder-leads-company-buyout/article4526784/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Garda to go private following $1.1-billion deal between founder, Apax Partners|url=http://business.financialpost.com/2012/09/07/garda-to-go-private-following-1-1-billion-deal-between-founder-apax-partners/}}</ref> in a $1.1 billion transaction<ref>{{cite web|title=Garda Security Gets $1.1 Billion Buyout Offer|url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2012/09/07/garda-security-gets-1-1-billion-buyout-offer/}}</ref> with support from [[private equity firm]] Apax Partners.<ref>{{cite web|title=Transaction to Take Garda Private by a Group Led by Company Founder, Chairman and CEO Stephan Cretier Completed|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/transaction-garda-private-group-led-221212069.html}}</ref>

